# Implementation Plan - Phase 2: User Authentication with JWT

We will build a secure authentication flow using JSON Web Tokens (JWT) for authentication and bcryptjs for password hashing. This includes the database user model, backend API routes, protective middleware, global frontend state using React Context API, user forms, and route guards.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Components

We will create the authentication controllers, routes, schemas, and helper utilities.

#### [NEW] [User.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/models/User.js)
Defines the structure for MongoDB user documents, including passwords that are salted and hashed.

#### [NEW] [generateToken.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/utils/generateToken.js)
A utility function to sign JWT tokens containing the user's database ID and role.

#### [NEW] [authController.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/controllers/authController.js)
Contains the request logic:
- `registerUser`: Validates input, hashes password, saves the user, and issues a JWT token.
- `loginUser`: Compares passwords, issues a JWT token.
- `getUserProfile`: Returns current user details from the decoded token (protected route).

#### [NEW] [authMiddleware.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/middleware/authMiddleware.js)
Express middleware to guard routes. It checks for a JWT in the `Authorization` header, decodes it, and attaches the user's database record to the request.

#### [NEW] [authRoutes.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/routes/authRoutes.js)
Configures Express endpoints for user operations:
- `POST /api/auth/register` (Public)
- `POST /api/auth/login` (Public)
- `GET /api/auth/profile` (Protected - requires valid JWT)

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/server.js)
Import and mount the authentication endpoints under the `/api/auth` path.

